;; Regression: (count (distinct v)) fuses to OP_COUNT_DISTINCT, whose small-
;; input kernel (cd_seq_count) hashed with the golden-ratio multiplier but
;; then masked the LOW bits of the product.  For integer-valued doubles the
;; IEEE-754 bit patterns are large power-of-two multiples (low bits zero), so
;; every value landed in one bucket → O(n^2) probing (a query-reachable DoS,
;; found by the eval fuzz target timing out on `count distinct` of til 65535
;; cast to F64).  Fixed to take the HIGH bits (Fibonacci hash).  These assert
;; the counts are exact — a clustered/broken hash would miscount.
(count (distinct (as (quote F64) [1 1 2 2 3 3 3]))) -- 3
(count (distinct (as (quote F64) (til 1000)))) -- 1000
(count (distinct (as (quote F64) (til 40000)))) -- 40000

;; Duplicated integer-valued doubles collapse correctly.
(count (distinct (as (quote F64) (% (til 5000) 100)))) -- 100

;; Integer count(distinct) still correct (unchanged path).
(count (distinct (til 40000))) -- 40000
